  "text": "## Apache Flink Windowing API Extension Points\n\n### 1. WindowAssigner Base Class\n**Location:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/WindowAssigner.java`\n\nThe abstract base class `WindowAssigner<T, W extends Window>` is the primary extension point for implementing custom window assignment logic. Developers must implement the following abstract methods:\n\n- **`Collection<W> assignWindows(T element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context)`** — Assigns zero or more windows to each incoming element based on the element, its timestamp, and the current processing time context.\n- **`Trigger<T, W> getDefaultTrigger()`** — Returns the default trigger for this window assigner (e.g., EventTimeTrigger for event-time windows).\n- **`TypeSerializer<W> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)`** — Provides serialization support for the window type.\n- **`boolean isEventTime()`** — Indicates whether windows are based on event time (true) or processing time (false).\n\nThe class also defines an inner `WindowAssignerContext` interface with a single method `getCurrentProcessingTime()` to support assigners that need wall-clock time.\n\n### 2. MergingWindowAssigner Subclass\n**Location:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/MergingWindowAssigner.java`\n\nThis abstract class extends `WindowAssigner<T, W extends Window>` and adds support for session-style window merging, required when windows can overlap and need to be combined. Key method:\n\n- **`void mergeWindows(Collection<W> windows, MergeCallback<W> callback)`** — Determines which windows should be merged. Implementations iterate over window candidates and call `callback.merge(Collection<W> toBeMerged, W mergeResult)` to signal merge operations. The callback includes an inner interface `MergeCallback<W>` with a single method `merge(Collection<W> toBeMerged, W mergeResult)`.\n\n### 3. Trigger Base Class\n**Location:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/triggers/Trigger.java`\n\nThe abstract base class `Trigger<T, W extends Window>` defines the lifecycle for window evaluation. Developers must implement:\n\n- **`TriggerResult onElement(T element, long timestamp, W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception`** — Called when an element arrives. Returns a TriggerResult indicating whether to fire, purge, or continue the window.\n- **`TriggerResult onEventTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception`** — Called when an event-time timer fires (watermark crosses registered time).\n- **`TriggerResult onProcessingTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception`** — Called when a processing-time timer fires (wall-clock time passes registered time).\n- **`void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception`** — Clears all state for the window, including registered timers.\n\nFor session windows, implement additionally:\n- **`boolean canMerge()`** — Returns true to indicate this trigger supports merging (overrides default false).\n- **`void onMerge(W window, OnMergeContext ctx) throws Exception`** — Called when windows are merged; must merge any trigger state using the provided `OnMergeContext` interface.\n\nThe `TriggerContext` interface provides access to state, timers, metrics, and watermark/processing-time information. The `OnMergeContext` extends `TriggerContext` to support `mergePartitionedState(StateDescriptor<S, ?> stateDescriptor)` for merging trigger state.\n\n### 4. EventTimeSessionWindows Reference Implementation\n**Location:** `flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/EventTimeSessionWindows.java`\n\nThis concrete implementation demonstrates the pattern:\n- **Class Declaration:** `public class EventTimeSessionWindows extends MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>`\n- **`assignWindows()` implementation:** Returns `Collections.singletonList(new TimeWindow(timestamp, timestamp + sessionTimeout))` — creates a single window from the element timestamp to timestamp + session timeout.\n- **`mergeWindows()` implementation:** Delegates to `TimeWindow.mergeWindows(windows, c)` — reuses utility logic to merge overlapping TimeWindows.\n- **Additional methods:** \n  - `getDefaultTrigger()` returns `EventTimeTrigger.create()`\n  - `isEventTime()` returns `true`\n  - Factory method `withGap(Duration size)` creates instances with a session timeout\n\n### 5. TimeWindow Class\n**Location:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java`\n\nThis class represents time-interval windows. Key features:\n- **Constructor:** `TimeWindow(long start, long end)` — creates a window [start, end), where start is inclusive and end is exclusive.\n- **Accessors:** `getStart()`, `getEnd()`, `maxTimestamp()` (returns end - 1)\n- **Utilities:** \n  - `intersects(TimeWindow other)` — tests overlap\n  - `cover(TimeWindow other)` — computes minimal covering window\n  - Static helper `mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` — sorts windows by start time and merges all overlapping windows, calling the callback for each merge operation.\n- **Serialization:** Includes an inner `Serializer` class for type serialization support.\n\n### Integration Flow\nA custom window assigner implementation follows this pattern:\n1. Extend `WindowAssigner` (or `MergingWindowAssigner` for session windows)\n2. Implement `assignWindows()` to produce window objects (typically TimeWindow instances)\n3. Return an appropriate `Trigger` subclass from `getDefaultTrigger()` (e.g., EventTimeTrigger)\n4. Provide a `TypeSerializer` for your window type\n5. If merging windows, extend `MergingWindowAssigner` and implement `mergeWindows()` to determine which windows overlap and should be combined\n6. If using a merging assigner, ensure the trigger's `canMerge()` returns true and `onMerge()` is properly implemented\n\nThe EventTimeSessionWindows class exemplifies this design: it assigns windows based on gaps in event time, delegates merging logic to TimeWindow utilities, and integrates with EventTimeTrigger for watermark-based window firing."
}

